defaultIntroduction defaultDeaf people 
defaultare 4 times more likely to be unemployed than the general population. The Job Centre Plus offer vital services that deaf people 
defaultrely on. UKCOD feel that the accessibility of these services for deaf people could be improved in a number of ways. 
defaultWe use the term “deaf” to mean all deaf people, including those who use BSL, those who lipread and may wear hearing aids or cochlear implan
defaultts, and those who are deafblind.
